{
  "text": "where g(s1, s2) is the number of injections between a set of size s1 into a set of size s2, i.e., g(s1, s2) = We note in passing that the chromatic polynomial of a cograph, and thus the number of colorings using the minimal number of colors, can be computed in polynomial time [CITATION_1] . There does not seem to be an obvious connection between the hc-colorings and the chromatic polynomial, however.",
  "correct_citation": {
